<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
Proposal for Non-posting entities day in Fear and Hate:<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
1).  One day a month per plane would be set aside for Indy/FFA raids.  Possibly the same day for both planes, discussion on this is welcome.<br>
<br>
2).  The Indy/FFA day ends at 2am PST (5am EST), just like any other day.  At this point everyone is expected to leave the zone.<br>
<br>
3).  All member's of current posting entities are expected to stay out of the plane on this day.  Unless a God is up and in that case, refer to the rule below about BB guilds.<br>
<br>
4).  If a God is up on an Indy/FFA raid day and the God had not been killed by 10 pm PST (1 am EST), then the BB guild that is currently up on rotation may come in and &quot;help&quot; those in the zone.  This rule is a change from the norm of the calendar because by definition an Indy/FFA will have no one entity that could call in the BB guild.  Loot procedures on this day should be the same as other BB call ins (BB guilds only get Epic Quest item, which items that consists of is being discussed elsewhere).<br>
<br>
5).  These rules are only for the Plane of Fear and the Plane of Hate.<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Please discuss these rules, and let me know if you think this is a viable solution.</font><P>Milambus Mandragon<BR>
